{"TopicId":179312,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Dual Screen support help","CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:28:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:28:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have 2 monitors. Everytime i have ksp running and i click on the second window, ksp goes away. Yes i have tried -popupwindow but it didnt help\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to have ksp in fullscreen without this happening?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shadowmage","CreatedById":138730,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:37:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223475933\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540578481\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184444\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Artienia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Artienia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes i have tried -popupwindow but it didnt help\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^^^ is the only way to do it with Unity games as far as I know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLikely you didn\u0027t run the option properly.\u00A0 If you posted your exact command line / run-as statement, it might allow for someone to diagnose why it isn\u0027t working.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:38:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223475938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540579034\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138730\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shadowmage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Shadowmage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^^^ is the only way to do it with Unity games as far as I know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLikely you didn\u0027t run the option properly.\u00A0 If you posted your exact command line / run-as statement, it might allow for someone to diagnose why it isn\u0027t working.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-popupwinndow\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nniinjaedit: ohno\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-26T18:38:30Z\u0022 title=\u002210/26/2018 06:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 26, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Artienia\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:43:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223475933\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540578481\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184444\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Artienia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Artienia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes i have tried -popupwindow but it didnt help\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn-game, in the graphics settings, you need to have \u0027fullscreen\u0027 disabled as well. Otherwise it will override the popupwindow parameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:44:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223475944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540579389\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn-game, in the graphics settings, you need to have \u0027fullscreen\u0027 disabled as well. Otherwise it will override the popupwindow parameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso you cant have it full screen?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tonka Crash","CreatedById":189552,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:56:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184444-artienia/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022184444\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184444-artienia/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Artienia\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I do this all the time on a laptop with 2 external monitors. In the game settings you turn off fullscreen, but set the resolution to your monitor\u0027s resolution. Then I have a shortcut on my desktop with the following for the Target\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022C:\\Games\\Kerbal Space Program\\KSP_x64.exe\u0022 -popupwindow\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like fullscreen, but doesn\u0027t minimize when you shift focus to another window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T18:57:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223475952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540580201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189552\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tonka Crash\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Tonka Crash said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184444-artienia/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022184444\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184444-artienia/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Artienia\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I do this all the time on a laptop with 2 external monitors. In the game settings you turn off fullscreen, but set the resolution to your monitor\u0027s resolution. Then I have a shortcut on my desktop with the following for the Target\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022C:\\Games\\Kerbal Space Program\\KSP_x64.exe\u0022 -popupwindow\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like fullscreen, but doesn\u0027t minimize when you shift focus to another window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwill try! thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shadowmage","CreatedById":138730,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-26T19:00:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223475944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540579389\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn-game, in the graphics settings, you need to have \u0027fullscreen\u0027 disabled as well. Otherwise it will override the popupwindow parameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice info -- I always had to fiddle with it a bit and/or use alt\u002Benter to get it into borderless-window mode after using the -popupwindow param.\u00A0 Probably that little bit that I was missing \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}